RESIDENTS taking rubbish to the dumpsite had no idea they were only metres away from a corpse.The body of a 67-year-old teacher was discovered at a dumpsite in KwaNdengezi, KZN.Nomasonto Ngwenya, a teacher at St James College, was reported missing on Friday by her daughter Nomfundo Ngwenya (30) after she disappeared from her house in BB Section, Umlazi.Her body was found on Tuesday. Cops said she had strangle marks on her neck.Resident Nomzamo Dladla (43) said she never thought a body would be found at the dump. &ldquo;What happened is shocking. It fills us with fear.&rdquo; Nomfundo said when her mum didn&rsquo;t answer her phone on Friday, she immediately went to the police. &ldquo;I hope the people who did this go to jail for a long time.&rdquo; Police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Zwane said: &ldquo;During the investigation the police spotted the gogo&rsquo;s Nissan Tiida in KwaNdengezi with four men sitting in it.&rdquo; The men were taken in for questioning and then took police to the dump site, where they had allegedly dumped her body. &ldquo;They were arrested and will appear in court soon,&rdquo; said Zwane.KZN acting police commissioner Major-General Bheki Langa said they will make sure the suspects get what they deserve.